  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency food assistance to flood affected population in North-eastern Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to ensure people are able to meet basic food and other essential needs following the floods. This WFP project provides 1) 178,160 people in shelters and camps with 85 MT of food assistance, 2) 93,324 people in homes with 784 MT of food assistance and US$ 480,870 in sector-specific unconditional cash transfers. The project provides life-saving assistance to 215,000 people, including 62,436 women, 59,598 men, 93,000 children, and 3,161 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
